                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/54.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am requested by the Minister for Foreign Affairs to send you the following: <pb
                        facs="1358" n="1242" xml:id="pg_1242"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Immediately upon learning that this Republic is to be honored by a visit
                            from the Secretary of State of the United States, this Government, in
                            appreciation thereof, appointed a committee of representative men to
                            receive Mr. Knox and tender to him and to the ladies and gentlemen of
                            his party a reception at the Government Palace, and also a banquet on
                            the 28th, besides such other courtesies as time may permit and they may
                            be willing to accept. The Government and people of Panama are delighted
                            with the prospect of the visit and, without political differences, are
                            all preparing in common to show their high appreciation of their honored
                            guest.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
